fields.name: Receive Time
fields.doc: Time the log was received at the management plane.

fields.name: Serial Number
fields.doc: Serial number of the firewall that generated the log.

fields.name: Type
fields.doc: Specifies type of log; values are traffic, threat, config, system and hip-match.

fields.name: Generated Time
fields.doc: Time the log was generated on the dataplane.

fields.name: Source User
fields.doc: Username of the user who initiated the session.

fields.name: Virtual System
fields.doc: Virtual System associated with the HIP match log.

fields.name: Machine Name
fields.doc: Name of the user’s machine.

fields.name: OS
fields.doc: The operating system installed on the user’s machine or device (or on the client system).

fields.name: Source IP
fields.doc: IP address of the source user.

fields.name: HIP
fields.doc: Name of the HIP object or profile.

fields.name: Repeat Count
fields.doc: Number of times the HIP profile matched.

fields.name: HIP Type
fields.doc: Whether the hip field represents a HIP object or a HIP profile.

fields.name: Sequence Number
fields.doc: A 64-bit log entry identifier incremented sequentially; each log type has a unique number space.

fields.name: Action Flags
fields.doc: A bit field indicating if the log was forwarded to Panorama.

fields.name: Device Group Hierarchy Level 1
fields.doc:
A sequence of identification numbers that indicate the device group’s location within a device group hierarchy. The firewall (or virtual system) generating the log includes the identification number of each ancestor in its device group hierarchy. The shared device group (level 0) is not included in this structure.
If the log values are 12, 34, 45, 0, it means that the log was generated by a firewall (or virtual system) that belongs to device group 45, and its ancestors are 34, and 12. To view the device group names that correspond to the value 12, 34 or 45, use one of the following methods:

fields.name: Virtual System Name
fields.doc: The name of the virtual system associated with the session; only valid on firewalls enabled for multiple virtual systems.

fields.name: Device Name
fields.doc: The hostname of the firewall on which the session was logged.

fields.name: Virtual System ID
fields.doc: A unique identifier for a virtual system on a Palo Alto Networks firewall.

fields.name: IPv6 Source Ip
fields.doc: IPv6 address of the user’s machine or device.
